OL,6,FIt was heard in court how the youth
OL,7,Fstarted to hit the bin man through the
OL,8,Fbroken window and Corden swung the axe
OL,9,Fthrough it. When the bin man lifted
OL,10,Fhis arm to protect himself, Corden hit
OL,11,Fthe man's arm and leg with the axe.
OL,13,FMr Tatlow continued: "The group were
OL,14,Fthen joined by Worthington, the last
OL,15,Fof the four to get out of Corden's
OL,16,Fcar. He fired a gun in the direction
OL,17,Fof the wagon.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/14
