OL,6,FA second victim has also finished
OL,7,Fwork. He suffered a stroke but doctors
OL,8,Fcould not say it was caused as a
OL,9,Fconsequence of the injuries or stress
OL,10,Ffrom the incident.
OL,12,FThe driver involved in the first
OL,13,Fattack returned to work in October
OL,14,F2023, after six months off. However,
OL,15,Fin May 2024 he had to leave work
OL,16,Fagain. He continues to receive
OL,17,Fcounselling and the court heard how
OL,18,Fit's unlikely he will be able to
OL,19,Freturn to work.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G11/14
